The Adichunchanagiri Mahasamsthan Mutt at Bellur in Nagamangala taluk has organised a series of programmes to mark the 71st birth anniversary of Balagangadharanatha Swami, who passed away in 2013.While Governor of Karnataka Vajubai Rudabai Vala will attend the function on January 17, Chief Minister Siddaramaiah will participate in another function on January 18. Programmes related to the celebrations commenced on Wednesday, Nirmalanandanatha Swami, peetadhipati of the mutt, has said.Speaking to presspersons on Thursday, he said that the mutt was organising a State-level childrenâ€™s literary meet, story reading and other events as part of the celebrations.Ministers H.K. Patil, M.H. Ambareesh and D.K. Shivakumar, and C.S. Puttaraju, MP, are expected to take part in the programme.